<https://synbiohub.org/public/igem/BBa_C0062> <http://wiki.synbiohub.org/wiki/Terms/synbiohub#mutableDescription> "In complex with HSL, LuxR binds to the Lux promoter, activating transcription      from Pr <bb_part>BBa_R0062</bb_part>, and repressing transcription from Pl <bb_part>BBa_R0063</bb_part>.   <p>The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The      right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This      expression is up-regulated by the action of the Lux activator, LuxR complexed      to HSL. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules the      signalling compound homoserine lactone (HSL). This complex binds to a palindromic      site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.</p>" .
<https://synbiohub.org/public/igem/BBa_C0062> <http://wiki.synbiohub.org/wiki/Terms/synbiohub#mutableNotes> "<P> <P>2 silent point mutants were introduced in the coding sequence to remove internal      XbaI and PstI sites. Mutation sites were chosen to replace codons commonly      used in <em>E. coli</em> with codons used at a similar frequency. <P>" .
<https://synbiohub.org/public/igem/BBa_C0062> <http://wiki.synbiohub.org/wiki/Terms/synbiohub#mutableProvenance> "<em>V. fischeri</em> <genbank>AF170104</genbank>" .
